why brandfolder?

brandfolder checks all the boxes

  • business model = subscription
  • technology = SaaS
  • total addressable market = anyone with a brand
  • provides distinct solution to meaningful problem
    • they come for asset management; they stay for the analytics

marketing

person scoring

  • in salesforce, leads & contacts are people
  • who are these people? what role do they have in buying decision?
  • what have they done? what is their campaign response history?

account scoring

  • combine people scores with account attributes
  • can grade accounts by industry, size, technology, age…

which events to invest in

  • each event requires an investment
  • each event should yield a return
    • brand awareness
    • lead acquisition
    • nurture

evaluating events

optimizing marketing investments

  • mind the lag
    • today’s investments may not yield bookings for months, years
  • milestones to measure
    • how did we acquire the person record?
    • what was first thing they responded to?
    • what did they respond to before the deal created?
    • what did they respond to after created but before won?

sales

territory and industry pitfalls to avoid

  • segmentation based on attributes that are not locked down
  • territories that do not account for account families
  • incoherent industry designations

land, retain, and expand measures

  • find attributes associated with churn risk: size? industry? usage?
  • timing and kind of expansion
    • at renewal?
    • more seats or add products?
  • plot cumulative year-over-year for seasonally adjusted compares

account taxonomies

  • which grew the most?
